## Key Features Demonstrated

### üéØ **HTML5 Datalist Support**
- **Explicit Declarations**: Reusable option lists with `@datalist[id="name" options="..."]`
- **Shorthand Auto-Generation**: Quick autocomplete with `@field{options}: [text]`
- **Smart Deduplication**: Automatic reuse of identical option lists
- **Security**: HTML-escaped options for XSS protection

### üöÄ **Enhanced Action Elements**
- **New Syntax**: `@[action "label"]` for clear semantic distinction
- **Styling Support**: Full CSS framework compatibility
- **JavaScript Integration**: onclick handlers and data attributes
- **Image Buttons**: Enhanced image input support

### üèóÔ∏è **Core-First Architecture**
- **FormManager**: Central API for all form operations
- **Event-Driven**: Real-time data binding and validation
- **Framework Agnostic**: Works with React, Vue, Angular, vanilla JS
- **Hidden Form Architecture**: Clean styling without wrapper interference

### ‚úÖ **Backward Compatibility**
- **Legacy Syntax**: All existing forms continue to work
- **Mixed Syntax**: New and old approaches work together
- **Progressive Enhancement**: Graceful fallback for older browsers
- **Migration Path**: Gradual adoption of new features

This comprehensive demo showcases the power and flexibility of FormDown's Phase 2 enhancements while maintaining the simplicity and markdown-first approach that makes FormDown unique.